      <hedline>
        <hl1>RTZ-CRA to Cut Back On Mining Exploration</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>RTZ-CRA Group, the world's largest mining company, said yesterday that it would shrink its exploration activities and eliminate 330 jobs in an attempt to  cut operating costs $50 million a year. The company, created by the acquisition  of CRA Ltd. of Australia by RTZ P.L.C. of Britain late last year, said a review  had found overlapping activities. RTZ-CRA spent $317 million last year on exploration.</p>
        <p>(Bloomberg Business News)</p>
      </block>
